From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 10:00:00 +0800
Subject: Force navigator.webdriver to return false in renderer

When running under PureCloak, unconditionally return false from
Navigator::webdriver() for defense-in-depth. The --enable-automation
flag and AutomationControlled blink feature are already disabled at
the browser level (via RenderProcessHostImpl and
ChromeContentBrowserClient patches). This patch adds a final layer
of defense at the renderer level to ensure navigator.webdriver is
never exposed to JavaScript, even if the browser-level protections
are bypassed or a future Chromium version changes how
AutomationControlled is implemented.

---
 third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc | 7 +------
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/navigator.cc
@@ -97,12 +97,7 @@ bool Navigator::cookieEnabled() const {
 }
 
 bool Navigator::webdriver() const {
-  if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::AutomationControlledEnabled())
-    return true;
-
-  bool automation_enabled = false;
-  probe::ApplyAutomationOverride(GetExecutionContext(), automation_enabled);
-  return automation_enabled;
+  return false;
 }
 
 String Navigator::GetAcceptLanguages() {
